            <hr>
    
            <div class="faqheader">
                    <h2>What is Virgil?</h2>
            </div> <!--end faqheader-->
         
            <hr>
          
            <div class="faqbox">
                    <p>A simpler, easier smartphone experience<br />
                     Virgil is a customizeable mobile interface designed to be easy and accessible to special needs individuals. <br />
                    Virgil offers direct, pre-programmed options from a main screen, and takes the guess work out of navigating a smartphone.</p><br />
            </div> <!--end faqbox-->
      
           <hr>
       
           <div class="faqheader">
                    <h2>Is it an app?</h2>
            </div> <!--end faqheader-->
          
            <hr>
           
            <div class="faqbox">
                    <p>Virgil is a browser based web app, not a native mobile app. <br />
                    Virgil will work on all major mobile browsers, regardless of phone type.</p><br />
            </div> <!--end faqbox-->
          
            <hr>
          
            <div class="faqheader">
                    <h2>What kind of information do I enter?</h2>
            </div> <!--end faqheader-->
           
            <hr>
           
            <div class="faqbox">
                    <p>Virgil lets you display important people, places, phone numbers, personal, and medical information. <br />
                    You only have to input the information you are comfortable with.</p><br />
            </div> <!--end faqbox-->
          
            <hr>
           
            <div class="faqheader">
                    <h2>Who is Virgil for?</h2>
            </div> <!--end faqheader-->
         
            <hr>
          
            <div class="faqbox">
                    <p>Virgil was designed as an aid for special needs individuals who have a difficult time navigating smartphones, but can benefit from the services they provide.<br />
                    As we designed Virgil, we expanded it to include the elderly, technologically wary, or anyone who finds smartphones confusng and just want to access a few core features.</p><br />
            </div> <!--end faqbox-->
           
            <hr>
           
            <div class="faqheader">
                    <h2>How can Virgil help me?</h2>
            </div> <!--end faqheader-->
         
            <hr>
          
            <div class="faqbox">
                    <p>Virgil presents a clear, unambiguous, easy to follow user interface for direct actions.<br />
                    Smartphones can be challenging for everyone, even more so for those with limited capabilities.<br />
                    Virgil bypasses the complex nature of the smartphone, simplifies the important functions, and presents clear, easy to read, one touch connection to important people, places, and information.</p><br />
            </div> <!--end faqbox-->
           
            <hr>
           
            <div class="faqheader">
                    <h2>Will Virgil work on my phone?</h2>
            </div> <!--end faqheader-->
         
            <hr>
         
           <div class="faqbox">
                    <p>If you have a smartphone (one with a current mobile web browser), Virgil will work on your phone.</p><br />
            </div> <!--end faqbox-->
          
            <hr>
          
            <div class="faqheader">
                    <h2>Can I edit my settings on my phone?</h2>
            </div> <!--end faqheader-->
        
            <hr>
         
            <div class="faqbox">
                    <p>Virgil is designed to be edited via desktop or tablet, and not by phone. <br />
                    The phone is the 'run' environment. <br />
                    For easiest setup and use, we recommend editing settings via desktop or tablet.</p><br />
            </div> <!--end faqbox-->
           
            <hr>
           
            <div class="faqheader">
                    <h2>Can I run Virgil on my Desktop?</h2>
            </div> <!--end faqheader-->
           
            <hr>
           
            <div class="faqbox">
                    <p>No. The desktop/tablet environment is meant for setup. We are a mobile service (for now.)</p><br />
            </div> <!--end faqbox-->
           
            <hr>
           
            <div class="faqheader">
                    <h2>Why do I have to confirm everything?</h2>
            
            </div> <!--end faqheader-->
            <hr>
           
            <div class="faqbox">
                    <p>Virgil is not a 'native' app, and cannot perform every action seamlessly (yet).<br />
                    We appreciate your patience as we continue to improve our product.</p><br />
            </div> <!--end faqbox-->
            
                 <hr>
                 
              <div class="faqheader">
                    <h2>Is there a Spanish version?</h2>
            </div> <!--end faqheader-->
            
            <hr>
           
            <div class="faqbox">
                    <p>Virgil is not yet available in Spanish. See our <a href="espanol.html">más información</a> page for more details. If you are interested in Virgil for another language, please send us an <a  href="mailto:dantashman@gmail.com">email</a> and we will alert you as soon as it becomes available.</p><br />
            </div> <!--end faqbox-->
            
            
      
            
